  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so we decided that it would be best if I-- if I go back, determine all those things, and find a job so that we could get married, thinking that, of course, fiancees of servicemen would-- would be allowed much sooner than others to-- to join them.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But as it turned out, we ran into just one obstacle after another.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and no consulates opened up in Germany for the next eight, nine months, so that we finally got to a point-- and Gerda first got to a point where she felt that she would not get out of Germany unless she found some other way, and heard through friends that if she could get into France, that she could find a consulate there, an American consulate, and-- which she did.",
      "word_count": 71
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when-- still absolutely-- it still took her-- there was just so much red tape involved that we decided-- I finally decided that the best way to solve this matter is if I went back this time to Paris, we would get married, and then Gerda could come.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that's what I did, not without many, many obstacles on both sides.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so we got married in June of '46.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it-- it occurred probably a week or 10 days after liberation.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Perhaps Gerda can remember the-- the time better than I can, but it was no more than that, in which they had sent her to an isolation ward in the hospital on another floor, where they sent people they expected to die.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it just so happens by this time, you know, I wasn't always sure of being able to see her every day.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
